                                                                            Python Lists

1> Lists = A list is a collection that allow multiple values to be stored
           inside a single variable.Lists are created  using square brackets
           [] and items are seprated by commas.


2> List Indexing
= Learned how to access individual elements from a list using their number.
  Python uses Zero-based indexing, meaning the first element start at
  index 0.

3> List Slicing
= Learned how to access multiple elements from a list using slicing.

 Syntax:

 list[start:end]


4> List Methods
= Learned commonly used list methods:

# append() = Adds a new item at the end of the list.

# insert() = Inserts an items at a specific position.

# remove() = Removes an item by its value.

# pop () = Removes the last item by default or aspecific index.

# clear() = Removes all items from the list.


5> Updating List Elements
= Learned how to replace an existing value in a list 
  using its index.

 Example = servers[1] = "Nginx Server"

This replaces the value at index 1 with a new value.

6> Loop with Lists
= Learned how to use a for loop to iterate through al elements in a list.

 Example:
for server in servers:
    print(server)
